Sichuan Encourages Foreign Participation in Reorganization
CHENGDU , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- The government of southwest China 's Sichuan Province has adopted a policy encouraging foreign businesses to participate in mergers , acquisitions and the reorganization of local enterprises .
A local official noted that the introduction of shareholding system has enabled local enterprises to gain direct access to financing and has in turn promoted Sichuan 's vigorous economic development .
Fifty-five local enterprises listed on the Shanghai , Shenzhen and Hong Kong stock exchanges have raised funds of well over 14.5 billion yuan .
" We warmly welcome foreign firms to participate in local enterprise reform , " according to the official .
